            <div id="id1" style="height: 43px; left: 20px; position: absolute; top: 20px; width: 515px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content Normal_External_515_43" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="Normal">
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; padding-top: 0pt; " class="Header">Call &amp; Raise</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="margin-left: 0px; position: relative; width: 1000px; z-index: 5; " id="body_layer">
            <div style="height: 0px; line-height: 0px; " class="bumper"> </div>
            <div id="id2" style="height: 415px; left: 20px; position: absolute; top: 12px; width: 504px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_2 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content Normal_External_504_415" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="Normal">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style"><br /></p>
                  <div class="paragraph paragraph_style" style="padding-bottom: 0pt; "><div style="height: 378px; width: 504px;  height: 378px; position: relative; width: 504px; " class="tinyText style_SkipStroke_1 inline-block"><img src="CallRaise_files/droppedImage.jpg" alt="" style="border: none; height: 379px; width: 505px; " /></div></div>
                </div>
                <div style="clear: both; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; " class="tinyText"> </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div id="id3" style="height: 389px; left: 535px; position: absolute; top: 15px; width: 427px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_427_389" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_1">A call or raise decision in poker is one of the building blocks for a newcomer. Consider the following play, where there is almost 1000 Rs in the pot and I have the cards 3 of <span class="style">clubs</span> and 2 of <span class="style">spades</span>. <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1">On the table flop cards have just been opened and we have “Ace of <span class="style">Spades</span>, Ace of <span class="style">Diamonds</span>, 3 of <span class="style">Spades</span>”<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1">The winning combinations at this point are<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1">  <span class="style">Pair of aces and pair of 3’s<br /></span></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1"><span class="style"><br /></span></p>
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_1"><span class="style">They can be beaten by any two pair or any single ace/double ace. Also it can be beaten by a 3 of hearts and other card higher than 2. </span></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div id="id4" style="height: 672px; left: 31px; position: absolute; top: 439px; width: 883px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_883_672" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_1"><span class="style_1">Decision: </span>A call or raise is made depending on the expected value of the money a player can earn. For example there is 1000 Rs in the pot and I have a 30% chance of winning the pot. The other players have raised 50 each and now it’s my turn to call or raise. <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_2">Case 1: I Call 50<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_2"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_3">Value = 30% * (1000+50 (from player 1)+50 (from player 2)) - 70%*50(assuming I call) = 295 (+ve)<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_2">Since I am considering current call / raise decision I don’t take 1000 into account. <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_2"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_2">Case 2: I Raise 25<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_2"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_3">Value = 30%*(1000+75+75) - 70%*75 = 292.5 (+ve)<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_2"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_2">Case 3: Raise 50<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_2"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_3">or 30%*(1000+100+100) - 70%*100 = 290 (+ve)<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1">This 30% estimate of course has to factor in the cards on the table and my guesses about other player cards. <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1">Breaking this into single round, we have a positive value of pot = 30%* 1000 = 300<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1">Negative value from 30%*100 - 70%*50 = -5, which is negative 5 per betting round I lose if I keep calling. <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1">If I raise this negative value rises, but still is lower than the expected value of the pot. <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1">Placing bets is similar to deciding the amount of leverage to put up on the stocks or how a portfolio manager invests in a multitude of stocks. <br /></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div id="id5" style="height: 452px; left: 30px; position: absolute; top: 1126px; width: 882px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_882_452" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_1">Other than that there is the art of bluffing where you bet aggressively on your weak cards. The logic being that some of the people with medium cards might “FOLD”. However winning also depends on two other things<br /></p>
                  <ol>
                    <li style="line-height: 26px; padding-left: 19px; text-indent: -19px; " class="full-width" value="1">
                      <p style="text-indent: -19px; " class="paragraph_style_4"><span style="font-size: 18px; " class="Bullet">1.</span><span style="width: 5px; " class="inline-block"></span>Your Bad / Medium cards rise up with Flop,Turn, River stage (similar to picking penny stocks or aggressive betting on penny stocks)<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 26px; padding-left: 19px; text-indent: -19px; " class="full-width" value="2">
                      <p style="text-indent: -19px; " class="paragraph_style_4"><span style="font-size: 18px; " class="Bullet">2.</span><span style="width: 5px; " class="inline-block"></span>Others fold so you eliminate some of the players<br /></p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1">Again after the flop, we can turn to above analysis of expected value of the pot to decide the call/raise decision. Personally I also don’t calculate probabilities on the fly so most of the numbers are memorized from wiki “Poker Hands”. Here is an approximate list of the numbers. <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_5"><br /></p>
                  <ol>
                    <li style="line-height: 22px; padding-left: 19px; text-indent: -19px; " class="full-width" value="1">
                      <p style="text-indent: -19px; " class="paragraph_style_6"><span style="font-size: 18px; " class="Bullet">1.</span><span style="width: 6px; " class="inline-block"></span> 3 of a kind - 3%<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 22px; padding-left: 19px; text-indent: -19px; " class="full-width" value="2">
                      <p style="text-indent: -19px; " class="paragraph_style_6"><span style="font-size: 18px; " class="Bullet">2.</span><span style="width: 6px; " class="inline-block"></span> Straight - 1%<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 22px; padding-left: 19px; text-indent: -19px; " class="full-width" value="3">
                      <p style="text-indent: -19px; " class="paragraph_style_6"><span style="font-size: 18px; " class="Bullet">3.</span><span style="width: 6px; " class="inline-block"></span>Flush - 0.5%<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 22px; padding-left: 19px; text-indent: -19px; " class="full-width" value="4">
                      <p style="text-indent: -19px; " class="paragraph_style_6"><span style="font-size: 18px; " class="Bullet">4.</span><span style="width: 6px; " class="inline-block"></span>Full House - 0.25%<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 22px; padding-left: 19px; text-indent: -19px; " class="full-width" value="5">
                      <p style="text-indent: -19px; " class="paragraph_style_6"><span style="font-size: 18px; " class="Bullet">5.</span><span style="width: 6px; " class="inline-block"></span>Two Pair - 8%<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 22px; padding-left: 19px; text-indent: -19px; " class="full-width" value="6">
                      <p style="text-indent: -19px; " class="paragraph_style_6"><span style="font-size: 18px; " class="Bullet">6.</span><span style="width: 6px; " class="inline-block"></span>One Pair - 50%<br /></p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_1"> </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div id="id6" style="height: 60px; left: 26px; position: absolute; top: 1588px; width: 888px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_888_60" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_1">Coming back to the cards at play, here are my calculations...<br /></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div style="height: 151px; width: 859px;  height: 151px; left: 30px; position: absolute; top: 1673px; width: 859px; z-index: 1; " class="tinyText style_SkipStroke_1">
              <img src="CallRaise_files/52.jpg" alt="" style="border: none; height: 151px; width: 860px; " />
            </div>
            


            <div id="id7" style="height: 164px; left: 33px; position: absolute; top: 1836px; width: 854px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_854_164" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_1">So I have 48% chance of winning the pot at this point. To be conservative I consider that the chance of winning is still around 40%, and place a bet of 50. Assuming that other two players call expected value <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1"><br /></p>
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_1">40%*1100 - 50*60% = 440 - 30 = 410 (+ve). So I can keep calling to keep the expected value positive. If they raise then again the probabilities change coz I have to take into account better possibility of higher cards for other players. </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
